{"author":{"id":"daecaa79b752289d08fa06c7a65c8d0387caf00b7e262b5741f4805727d0a582"},"ops":[{"type":2,"timestamp":1746985095,"nonce":"atzvH4BuDuaH10DPTn6S7bK+8i0=","metadata":{"github-id":"RTE_lADOCGKeh86BtRiozwAAAAQZaUzk"},"title":"Windows: \"access denied\" when creating a bug","was":"Windows: \"access denied\" when creating a bug"},{"type":5,"timestamp":1746985482,"nonce":"QmStf0eVvyXHT64KUPSJ5N9mehs=","metadata":{"github-id":"UNLE_lADOCGKeh86BtRiozwAAAAQZaXz5"},"added":[],"removed":["priority/awaiting-more-evidence"]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1746985482,"nonce":"GL3w6l/D0MYbIE78E3lN3GS4E6Y=","metadata":{"github-id":"UNLE_lADOCGKeh86BtRiozwAAAAQZaXz7"},"added":[],"removed":["triage/needs-information"]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1746985482,"nonce":"4K4UntXfFvl3/WBKdzodAiUT22g=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOCGKeh86BtRiozwAAAAQZaXz-"},"added":["priority/backlog"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1746985482,"nonce":"HO9Mw3+Kx58tNDkcZ45vAMl0yho=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOCGKeh86BtRiozwAAAAQZaX0A"},"added":["triage/accepted"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1746985482,"nonce":"M4eRI2LHgx7leRacsmSHk8NjOdg=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOCGKeh86BtRiozwAAAAQZaX0D"},"added":["platform/windows"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1746985617,"nonce":"2LErvkMpfITVXBcfIHpVeXcMJp8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOCGKeh86rER0m","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/1142#issuecomment-2870025510"},"message":"\u003e Is it okay to mess with files like this? I thought that this tool could be cleanly integrated into a git environment.\n\u003e I want to use this tool but if it is going to clash with git in some way, I'm not really sure if I should use it.\n\n`git-bug` shouldn't ever attempt to touch objects that it didn't create. so if the \"safety\" you're thinking of is related to your working tree and/or normal git commits and objects, yes, git-bug is safe.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1746990225,"nonce":"cf2mLDd8FEzgtyH2apfOJaV9aOE=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOCGKeh86rEYiw","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/1142#issuecomment-2870053040"},"message":"regarding this issue:\n\nas of `v0.8.1`, the \"create a new bug\" workflow is pretty simple. it handles a bit of logic like getting and cleaning up the title and body, and then calls a `go-git` method to handle the actual object creation.\n\nso, i think this is likely to be a go-git issue. i found this issue, which seems to be directly related: https://github.com/go-git/go-git/issues/55. unfortunately, it doesn't have a linked commit indicating it was closed.\n\nit [appears](https://github.com/src-d/go-git/issues/1155) that a workaround might be to use \"git bash\", but that obviously isn't ideal if you're used to powershell and want to keep using it.\n\ni don't have a windows machine (physical or virtual) to recreate this issue, so unfortunately, i can't really debug or iterate on go-git's internals to work out a fix at the moment.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1746990257,"nonce":"N4UT6q3gsxxeGcQ5BMMEpbF/CNQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOCGKeh86rEYiwzmaCwhU"},"target":"fbe82494ea9e7fc108f51de89e4140147809eb2f4f07acda2a9e7650afb3c9c9","message":"regarding this issue:\n\nas of `v0.8.1`, the \"create a new bug\" workflow is pretty simple. it handles a bit of logic like getting and cleaning up the title and body, and then calls a `go-git` method to handle the actual object creation.\n\nso, i think this is likely to be a go-git issue. i found this issue, which seems to be directly related: https://github.com/go-git/go-git/issues/55. unfortunately, it doesn't have a linked commit indicating it was resolved (it was just closed due to inactivity).\n\nit [appears](https://github.com/src-d/go-git/issues/1155) that a workaround might be to use \"git bash\", but that obviously isn't ideal if you're used to powershell and want to keep using it.\n\ni don't have a windows machine (physical or virtual) to recreate this issue, so unfortunately, i can't really debug or iterate on go-git's internals to work out a fix at the moment.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1746991918,"nonce":"Lapnsu/G6Pqs/e/ttOB/ocJ2xj8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOCGKeh86rEbDu","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/1142#issuecomment-2870063342"},"message":"@MichaelMure do you have any insight to add here? i think a viable workaround in the short term to unblock users would be to call the git command line for this (on windows only, as in, a separate func with a `//go:build windows` directive).","files":null}]}